TI Hypertrophic osteoarthropathy in adults with cystic fibrosis.
SO Thorax. 1976 Oct. 31(5). P 572-5.
MJ CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: co.  OSTEOARTHROPATHY-SECONDARY-HYPERTROPHIC: di.
MN ADULT.  ARTHRITIS: di.  CASE-REPORT.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: ra.
   DIAGNOSIS-DIFFERENTIAL.  FIBULA: ra.  HUMAN.  MALE.
   OSTEOARTHROPATHY-SECONDARY-HYPERTROPHIC: ra.  TIBIA: ra.
AB Three adult patients with cystic fibrosis presented with arthralgia,
   and investigation for the usual causes of arthritis proved negative.
   Radiographs of long bones revealed periostitis and new bone fromation
   characteristic of hypertrophic osteoarthropathy. Symptomatic
   improvement occurred after analgesic and anti-inflammatory therapy.
   In patients with cystic fibrosis and bone or joint pain, the
   diagnosis of hypertrophic osteoarthropathy should be considered and
   long bone radiographs obtained.
